  <title>GWeather.Location.prototype.serialize</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function serialize(): <link href="../GLib-2.0/GLib.Variant.html">GLib.Variant</link> {
    // Gjs wrapper for gweather_location_serialize()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Transforms a <link xref="GWeather.Location"/> into a <link href="../GLib-2.0/GLib.Variant.html">GLib.Variant</link>, in a way that
calling <link xref="GWeather.Location.deserialize"/> will hold an equivalent
<link xref="GWeather.Location"/>.
The resulting variant can then be stored into GSettings or on disk.
This call is only valid for cities, weather stations and detached
locations.
The format of the resulting <link href="../GLib-2.0/GLib.Variant.html">GLib.Variant</link> is private to libgweather,
and it is subject to change. You should use the "v" format in GSettings,
to ensure maximum compatibility with future versions of the library.</p>

